Download LTC

  The whole system is packaged in {{{./downloads/LTC-${project.version}.jar}LTC-${project.version}.jar}}.

  The system can be used via the included LTC Editor or with Emacs. The JAR file contains the necessary
  Emacs Lisp files for <<<ltc-mode>>>.  You can extract those files
  with the <<<jar>>> tool (as explained in the {{{./html_multipage/manual/manualch1.html}installation chapter of the manual}})
  or you may download the files individually here:

  * {{{./downloads/emacs/xml-rpc.el}xml-rpc.el}}

  * {{{./downloads/emacs/versions.el}versions.el}}

  * {{{./downloads/emacs/ltc-mode.el}ltc-mode.el}}

  []

  Or, use the {{{./downloads/ltc-install.sh}ltc-install.sh}} Bash script to automatically fetch the latest JAR file to
  a location of your choice and optionally extract the Emacs Lisp files to your Emacs directory.
  You can obtain usage information by invoking the script this way:

+----
$> sh ltc-install.sh -h
+----

* System Requirements

*---------------------------+------------------------------------+-----------------------+
| <<Java>>                  | 1.6 or above                       | <<<$> java -version>>>
| (JDK if using <<<jar>>>)  |                                    |
*---------------------------+------------------------------------+-----------------------+
| <<git>>                   | 1.7.2 or above                     | <<<$> git --version>>>
*---------------------------+------------------------------------+-----------------------+
| <<Emacs>>                 | 23 or above; no support for XEmacs |
| (if using <<<ltc-mode>>>) |                                    |
*---------------------------+------------------------------------+-----------------------+

  We have tested the system on Mac OS X and Linux.  It is designed to run on Unix platforms.  Windows is not supported
  although it may run with a Unix-like shell under Windows.

